.TH GH-REPO 1 "February 2026" "gh-repo-create" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gh-repo \- Create and manage GitHub repositories from the command line

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gh-repo
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBgh-repo\fR is a C++ CLI tool for creating and managing GitHub repositories.
It supports both interactive REPL mode and command-line flags.

.SH OPTIONS

.SS General Options
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.RS
Show help message and exit
.RE

.SS Repository Operations
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-path\fR \fI<dir>\fR
.RS
Path to local git repository (default: current directory)
.RE

\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-name\fR \fI<name>\fR
.RS
Repository name
.RE

\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-description\fR \fI<desc>\fR
.RS
Repository description (max 350 characters)
.RE

\fB\-\-public\fR
.RS
Make repository public
.RE

\fB\-\-private\fR
.RS
Make repository private
.RE

\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-list\fR
.RS
List all your GitHub repositories
.RE

\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-delete\fR \fI<name>\fR
.RS
Delete a repository by name
.RE

\fB\-\-ssh\-only\fR
.RS
Push via SSH only, skip GitHub API calls
.RE

.SH REPL COMMANDS

When run without arguments, \fBgh-repo\fR enters interactive REPL mode:

.TP
\fBcreate\fR (\fBc\fR)
Create a new GitHub repository
.TP
\fBlist\fR (\fBl\fR)
List all your GitHub repositories
.TP
\fBdelete\fR (\fBd\fR)
Delete a GitHub repository
.TP
\fBssh\fR (\fBs\fR)
Push via SSH only (no API calls)
.TP
\fBauth\fR
Manage authentication
.TP
\fBhelp\fR (\fB?\fR)
Show help message
.TP
\fBexit\fR
Exit the REPL

.SH CONFIGURATION

.SS Token Authentication

The tool requires a GitHub Personal Access Token. Set it via:

.TP
Environment variable:
.EX
export GH_TOKEN="your_token"
.EE

.TP
Or config file (~/.gh-repo-create.json):
.EX
{"token": "your_token"}
.EE

.SS Token Scope Requirements

.TP
Create/List: \fBrepo\fR scope
.TP
Delete: \fBdelete_repo\fR scope

.SH FILES

.TP
~/.gh-repo-create.json
Token configuration file
.TP
~/.gh-repo-create-history
Command history (REPL mode)

.SH EXAMPLES

.SS Create a repository
.EX
gh-repo -p ./my-project -n my-repo --public
.EE

.SS List repositories
.EX
gh-repo --list
.EE

.SS Delete a repository
.EX
gh-repo --delete old-repo
.EE

.SS SSH-only push
.EX
gh-repo --ssh-only -p .
.EE

.SS Interactive mode
.EX
$ gh-repo
gh-repo> list
gh-repo> help
gh-repo> exit
.EE

